3 Modeling

Utilized svyglm() to analyze and display the relationship between the “Results” and variables. We present the summary and ANOVA table of models including coefficients of the levels for each variable, degree of freedom, etc. On those tables, more * comes less p-value. (Signif. codes: ***\(\small< 0.001\), ** \(\small< 0.01\), * \(\small<0.05\), . \(\small<0.1\), and otherwise.)

3.1 ORTIME

Operation time in minutes. The estimated coefficients for age, BMI, approach (robot and senhance-robot), technique, laterality, and hernia types have low p-values. Clearly, patients over 70 years of age and those with overweight BMI affect operation time. Negative coefficients are observed for approach (senhance-robot), technique (TEP), laterality (unilateral), and sex (male). Focusing on the approach, using the senhance-robot clearly reduces the operation time compared to using the robot.
